# CornerList Project Overview

## Stack

Next.js 16 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, Supabase (Auth, Postgres, Storage). Deployed on Vercel.

## Architecture

Feature-based folder structure with barrel exports:

```
src/
  app/              Next.js routes (/, /search, /djs/[id], /join-dj)
  components/       Shared UI (Navbar) — barrel-exported via index.ts
  features/
    search/         components/, data/, utils/, __tests__/
    dj-profile/     components/, data/, __tests__/
    join-dj/        components/, __tests__/
  types/            Shared TS types (Genre, Dj, Review)
e2e/                Playwright specs
```

## Import convention

Always import from barrel exports, never deep paths:

```ts
import { SearchHero, MOCK_DJS } from "@/features/search";
import { Navbar } from "@/components";
import { Genre, Dj } from "@/types";
```

## Data colocation

Mock data lives inside the owning feature (`features/search/data/`, `features/dj-profile/data/`). Utilities live in `features/*/utils/`. Cross-feature access goes through barrel exports.

## Requirements

`cornerlist-mvp-prd.md` is the source of truth for all product requirements, data model, and API contracts.

## Current phase

Phase 1 (UI + testing) is **complete** — 12 components, 84 tests passing. Phase 2 (Supabase backend + API routes) is next.
